<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="965" pageId="20" pageNumber="964" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[816,1460,482,1973]" pageId="20" pageNumber="964">
<emphasis box="[862,941,1419,1442]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="964">Note. –</emphasis>
The type of 
<taxonomicName box="[1088,1309,1418,1442]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Iresine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="20" pageNumber="964" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="edmonstonei">
<emphasis box="[1088,1309,1418,1442]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="964">Iresine edmonstonei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that was collected by Edmonston might have been from a plant introduced by early settlers or the specimen was mislabeled to originate from Galapagos (
<bibRefCitation author="Eliasson, U. H." box="[1004,1165,1512,1536]" journalOrPublisher="Bot. J. Linn. Soc." pageId="20" pageNumber="964" pagination="41 5 - 4 33" part="91" refId="ref25281" refString="Eliasson, U. H. 1985. Identity and taxonomic affinity of some members of the Amaranthaceae from the Galapagos Islands. Bot. J. Linn. Soc. 91: 41 5 - 4 33. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.1985. tb 01011. x" title="Identity and taxonomic affinity of some members of the Amaranthaceae from the Galapagos Islands" type="journal article" year="1985">Eliasson, 1985</bibRefCitation>
). The folder of 
<emphasis box="[1335,1430,1512,1536]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="964">I. elatior</emphasis>
in the Willdenow herbarium (B) contains four sheets, only two of which have labels. Sheet 0 4 is the only one with a label saying “ 
<taxonomicName box="[905,978,1606,1629]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Iresine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="20" pageNumber="964" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[905,978,1606,1629]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="964">Iresine</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– spec. nova”. The fact that the folder itself contains on its inside three more labels, out of the hand of Bonpland as well as Schlechtendahl (H.W. Lack, pers. comm.) is a further indication of a different origin of the sheets but also that these three labels cold not unambiguously be assigned to any of the sheets. A lectotypification is therefore warranted. The geographic origin of the specimens is unknown. The type specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[954,1077,1824,1848]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Iresine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="20" pageNumber="964" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="laxissima">
<emphasis box="[954,1077,1824,1848]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="964">I. laxissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is from a hermaphroditic plant and has only bisexual flowers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[816,1460,482,1973]" lastBlockId="21.[173,816,202,351]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="965" pageId="20" pageNumber="964">
The name “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Klotzsch" authorityName="Klotzsch" box="[988,1299,1886,1910]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Rosea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="20" pageNumber="964" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poeppigiana">
<emphasis box="[988,1194,1887,1910]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="964">Rosea poeppigiana</emphasis>
Klotzsch
</taxonomicName>
” is not validly published but was listed by 
<bibRefCitation box="[1118,1273,1917,1942]" pageId="20" pageNumber="964" refId="ref28405" refString="Seubert, M. 1875 (&quot; 1855 - 1875 &quot;). Amaranthaceae. Pp. 16 1 - 2 52 in: Martius, C. F. P. de &amp; Eichler, A. G. (eds.), Flora Brasiliensis, vol. 5 (1). Monachii [Munich]; Lipsiae [Leipzig]: apud Fried. Fleischer. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="book chapter">Seubert (1875)</bibRefCitation>
as a synonym of 
<emphasis box="[816,904,1949,1973]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="964">I. elatior</emphasis>
Rich. ex Willd. There is a specimen in B (
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="965" pageId="20" pageNumber="964">E.F. Poeppig s.n.</emphasis>
, B 10 0 242399, from Brazil, Pará) annotated with the name “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Kl." authorityName="Kl." box="[184,431,233,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Rosea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="965" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poeppigiana">
<emphasis box="[184,388,233,256]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="965">Rosea poeppigiana</emphasis>
Kl.
</taxonomicName>
”. The handwriting is clearly by J.F. Klotzsch (R. Vogt, pers. comm.). Seubert cited this name as it was often practised at the time.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[173,816,202,351]" box="[218,816,326,351]" pageId="21" pageNumber="965">Taxonomic status: Species limits not yet studied in detail (B).</paragraph>
